<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The method Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_HelperAbstract#_normalizeId($value) builds IDs for the anchor tags of the navigation elements according to the following pattern:</p>

<p>$prefix + "-" + $value</p>

<p>The developer can just set the $value. The $prefix is always the lower cased name of the navigation helper type (e.g. "menu" for Menu or "breadcrumbs" for Breadcrumbs).</p>

<p>It would be great to have the ability to customize the complete ID and not only the part after the hyphen.</p>

    </div>
